The paper proposes a new input perturbation mechanism for achieving differential privacy in principal component analysis. This involves generating matrix noise using a Wishart distribution. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
